<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06227133 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06227133 </ACCESS><DESCRIPT>  LOUISIANA; JURY; RULING; RACIAL; VIOLENCE  </DESCRIPT><LEADPARA>  A federal grand jury in Louisiana has indicted five Ku Klux Klan members oncivil rights charges stemming from cross burnings at schools, a courthouse andother places, the Justice Department said Tuesday.;    The five are members ofthe Invisible Empire Knights of the Ku Klux Klan, including its reputed GrandDragon, or state leader, Wayne Pierce, and its No. 2 official, Terry Litton,the Justice Department said.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  5 KLANSMEN CHARGED WITH CROSS BURNINGS  </HEADLINE><TEXT>     Nine crosses were burned May 7 and 8 around Shreveport, La., to intimidateblacks, the indictment charges.;    It said Pierce ordered the crosses burnedon the day he was to go to jail on a federal firearms conviction.;    Thecrosses were burned at the Shreveport headquarters of the National Associationfor the Advancement of Colored People, two public schools, the home of a blackfamily, the federal courthouse in Shreveport, the Central Christian Church, anapartment complex and along two roadways.  </TEXT><BYLINE>  Associated Press  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><CITY>  Washington  </CITY><EDITION>  Morning Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   910814  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  August  </MONTH><PG.COL>  6A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  149  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday August 14, 199100227133,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>